</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-23_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-24_ pf-text-1">The ACW distributes over £30 million annually in grants and funding to arts organisations, projects, and individual artists.




</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-26_ pf-text-1">Wales's arts and culture sector contributes approximately £1.7 billion to the Welsh economy each year.


<strong>
</strong></li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-28_ pf-text-1">Over 70% of adults in Wales participate in or attend arts events, demonstrating the significant public engagement driven by the ACW.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-30_ pf-text-1">The ACW supports numerous educational programmes that reach tens of thousands of children and young people annually, fostering the next generation of Welsh artists and creatives.



</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-32_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-33_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-34_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key definitions
</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-36_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">To fully appreciate the work of the Arts Council of Wales, it is essential to understand some core terms:



























</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-38_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-39_ pf-text-1"><strong>Grants</strong> - Financial awards given to individuals or organisations to support specific projects or operational costs.




</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-41_ pf-text-1"><strong>Arts organisations</strong> - Institutions or groups dedicated to creating, producing, or promoting art in various forms, including visual arts, music, theatre, and literature.

<strong>
</strong></li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-43_ pf-text-1"><strong>Compliance</strong> - Adherence to laws, regulations, and guidelines that govern the operations of arts organisations and the use of public funds.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-45_ pf-text-1"><strong>Legislation </strong>- Laws enacted by a legislative body that impact the operations and governance of arts institutions.


